### PeerPay API Gateway Endpoint
@gatewayUrl = http://localhost:8080
@jwtToken = <PASTE_JWT_TOKEN_HERE>
@payerId = <PASTE_PAYER_ID_HERE>
@payeeId = <PASTE_PAYEE_ID_HERE>
@transactionId = <PASTE_TRANSACTION_ID_HERE>

### 1. Register Payer (User A)
POST {{gatewayUrl}}/api/v1/users/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Arjun Kumar",
  "email": "arjun@peerpay.com",
  "phone": "9876543210",
  "upiId": "arjun@peerpay",
  "password": "secure_password"
}

### 2. Register Payee (User B)
POST {{gatewayUrl}}/api/v1/users/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "Neha Sharma",
  "email": "neha@peerpay.com",
  "phone": "9876543211",
  "upiId": "neha@peerpay",
  "password": "secure_password"
}

### 3. Login to Authenticate (User A)
# Response returns JWT token under `data.token`. Copy and set as @jwtToken above.
POST {{gatewayUrl}}/api/v1/users/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "arjun@peerpay.com",
  "password": "secure_password"
}

### 4. Fetch User Profile
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/api/v1/users/{{payerId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{jwtToken}}

### 5. Fetch User Profile by UPI ID
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/api/v1/users/upi/neha@peerpay
Authorization: Bearer {{jwtToken}}

### 6. Initiate Payment
# Requires unique X-Idempotency-Key header.
# Copy generated transactionId from response and paste into @transactionId above.
POST {{gatewayUrl}}/api/v1/payments/initiate
Authorization: Bearer {{jwtToken}}
X-Idempotency-Key: tx_idempotency_key_1001
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "payerId": "{{payerId}}",
  "payeeId": "{{payeeId}}",
  "payerUpiId": "arjun@peerpay",
  "payeeUpiId": "neha@peerpay",
  "amount": 500.00,
  "remarks": "Lunch share"
}

### 7. Test Idempotency (Re-send Step 6)
# Sending request again with identical header key returns cached result directly.
POST {{gatewayUrl}}/api/v1/payments/initiate
Authorization: Bearer {{jwtToken}}
X-Idempotency-Key: tx_idempotency_key_1001
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "payerId": "{{payerId}}",
  "payeeId": "{{payeeId}}",
  "payerUpiId": "arjun@peerpay",
  "payeeUpiId": "neha@peerpay",
  "amount": 500.00,
  "remarks": "Lunch share"
}

### 8. Simulate UPI PSP Network Success Callback
# Triggers state transition to COMPLETED & publishes completion event to Kafka.
POST {{gatewayUrl}}/api/v1/payments/{{transactionId}}/complete
Authorization: Bearer {{jwtToken}}

### 9. Simulate UPI PSP Network Failure Callback
# Triggers state transition to FAILED.
POST {{gatewayUrl}}/api/v1/payments/{{transactionId}}/fail?reason=INSUFFICIENT_FUNDS&errorCode=FAIL_401
Authorization: Bearer {{jwtToken}}

### 10. Check Payer Balance (Ledger Service)
# Balance is computed double-entry (Sum of Credits - Sum of Debits). Should show debit of ₹500.
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/api/v1/ledger/balance/{{payerId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{jwtToken}}

### 11. Check Payee Balance (Ledger Service)
# Should show credit of ₹500.
GET {{gatewayUrl}}/api/v1/ledger/balance/{{payeeId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{jwtToken}}

### 12. Run Reconciliation Verification
# Reconciles transaction status against double-entry ledger entries.
GET http://localhost:8085/api/v1/reconciliation/validate/{{transactionId}}

### 13. Query DLQ Backlog Audit
# View message failures captured by the DLQ consumer.
GET http://localhost:8085/api/v1/reconciliation/dlq
